		<blockquote class="restore">Cheating is pretty rampant in college; I don't think it is really a big deal though that that is the case though as what is primarily cheated on is not worth a ton of points and you still have to study a lot to pass exams and do well on projects.  I think cheating ( at least in engineering) is primarily motivated by time efficiency rather than an inability to do the work or incompetence.  The volume of work required is obscene between reports and tests and projects and homework and quizzes, then on top of that organization and club requirements, developing and maintaining social networks for future career purposes.  It's very strenuous and stressful.</blockquote>
	</div>
