		<blockquote class="restore">As an aside, I much prefer classes that are designed around projects and fewer exams and that have ungraded HW.  Regular quizzes that are mainly geared towards tracking attendance are great too.  A lot of classes first testing of student's knowledge is graded though and as a result encourages cheating to maintain high scores and get easy points that ultimately inflate class averages.</blockquote>
	</div>
